snippet.textDisplay:
This song reminds me of life, the way she has sang it over the years it always seems like she has added her experiences of life to her voice. At 80 plus years Madam Khanum's voice reflects all those bygone days, all the love both received and those unrequited. The deaths of many loved ones.
Life is such a bitter sweet tale.

snippet.textDisplay:
I've listened to this so many times today and I wondered what makes it so insatiable? Well, I think it's the ability of Farida sahiba to make us emote with the song. I was transported years behind to when a guy I loved with all my soul, left me. 

The song sure makes me melancholy but, it makes me also not hate him, but instead cherish what we had together. It makes me believe in love again. 

Khuda afiz, madam. May you live long and continue to grace us with your music. Much love and respect from an Indian girl.
